<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="eager-adj">eager <strong><em>adj</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /'iːɡə(r)/    美 /'iːɡər/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>渴望的；热切的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>His classes were crowded with eager students. 
他的课上挤满了求知若渴的学生。</p></div>

<ul>
<li>(be) eager to do sth:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Mike is eager to stay away from the busy city life for a while. 
迈克渴望暂时远离繁忙的城市生活。</p></div>

<ul>
<li>(be) eager for sth:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He is eager for success. 
他渴望成功。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">派生词汇</h2>
<p>eagerly /'iːgəlɪ/ adv <br />
eagerness /'iːgənəs/ n   </p>
<h2 id="_3">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>The teacher is glad that everyone in her class is<strong><em>_</em></strong>_(渴望的) to learn.  （2010 陕西）  </li>
<li>Some of us were confident and eager take part in the class activity.<strong><em>_</em></strong>_(改错题）  （2018 全国）  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. eager  2. eager后加to  </p></div>